# Feature Documentation

Major features **must** be documented in `docs/features/` in the **same PR** as implementation.

## Read before extending

Before modifying auth, memories, voice, illustrations, family profiles, notifications, or onboarding:

1. Check [docs/features/README.md](../../docs/features/README.md) index
2. Read the relevant `docs/features/<name>.md`
3. Read TECH_SPEC for API/schema contracts

## Write when shipping

Copy [docs/features/_template.md](../../docs/features/_template.md). Document:

- Purpose, user behavior, architecture flow
- Tables, Edge Functions, client hooks/routes (file paths)
- **Extension guide** — how future features should integrate
- Constraints, async behavior, security gotchas

Update the index in `docs/features/README.md`.

## Tests

Same PR: unit + integration (+ e2e if user-facing). See [docs/TESTING.md](../../docs/TESTING.md).

## Major vs trivial

| Document | Skip |
|----------|------|
| New flow, Edge Function, AI pipeline, cross-feature dependency | Copy/style-only, single-line fixes |

If an agent would need 3+ files to understand integration → write the doc.
